PJSIP (pjproject)
=================

PJSIP is a free and open-source multimedia communication library
by Teluu Ltd. and contributors. It implements SIP, SDP, RTP, STUN,
TURN, and ICE.

synthmodem redistributes a compiled binary built from PJSIP version
2.15.1 inside `vm/prebuilt/` (specifically, the `d-modem` helper that
links against PJSIP statically). The source tarball is vendored at
`vm/sources/pjproject-2.15.1.tar.gz` and is byte-identical to the
upstream release tag:

  https://github.com/pjsip/pjproject/archive/refs/tags/2.15.1.tar.gz

Upstream project:  https://github.com/pjsip/pjproject
Upstream license:  https://docs.pjsip.org/en/latest/overview/license.html

License
-------

PJSIP is dual-licensed:

  1. GNU General Public License, version 2 (or later), as published
     by the Free Software Foundation.
  2. A commercial license from Teluu Ltd.

synthmodem redistributes PJSIP under the GPL-2.0-or-later option.
The complete GPL-2.0 text that applies is the same one that covers
synthmodem itself, at `licenses/GPL-2.0.txt`. PJSIP's upstream
COPYING file is verbatim identical to that text.

Each PJSIP source file carries its own copyright header (typically
"Copyright (C) 2003-xxxx Teluu Inc. (http://www.teluu.com)") and
license grant. Those headers are preserved in the vendored tarball.

Corresponding source
--------------------

GPL-2.0 §3(a) requires that the PJSIP binary redistributed in
`vm/prebuilt/` travel with its complete corresponding source. That
obligation is satisfied by committing the pinned source tarball to
this repository at `vm/sources/pjproject-2.15.1.tar.gz`. See
`vm/sources/README.md` and the top-level `COPYING` for the full
corresponding-source statement.

Our build configuration
-----------------------

synthmodem customizes the PJSIP build only through a compile-time
configuration file, `vm/pjsip/config_site.h` (currently empty, matching
what D-Modem ships). No PJSIP source files are modified. See
`vm/pjsip/UPSTREAM.txt` for the build recipe.
